(539, 3, '2014-04-03 20:32:30', '2014-04-03 20:32:30', 'Since 2005, Brevard Zoo in partnership with UCF has taken on the task of implementing restoration mats to build oyster reefs in Volusia County.Â  This process begins by raking down and leveling layers of accumulated dead oysters, known as dead margins, in order to anchor down oyster mats where oysters can have a permanent home without the possibility of future disturbance.\n\n<a href="http://darrengriffith.net/wp/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/OysterMat1.png"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-53" alt="OysterMat1" src="http://darrengriffith.net/wp/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/OysterMat1-300x192.png" width="300" height="192" /></a>\n\nSections of aquaculture grade mesh containing 36 empty oyster shells attached using zip ties are used to create the oyster mats that are placed on the estuary floor. The oyster mats provide a hard substrate for oyster larvae to attach to and begin to build a new reef. Oysters are gregarious species, meaning they live in groups, so the placement of shells in these areas, attracts the free floating larvae. These mats are so effective that not only will they withstand disruption from boats, but they will not even be dislodged by hurricanes.Â  As such, use of oyster mats is a means of permanent restoration of the oyster reefs.\n\n<a href="http://darrengriffith.net/wp/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/OysterMat2.png"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-54" alt="OysterMat2" src="http://darrengriffith.net/wp/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/OysterMat2-300x229.png" width="300" height="229" /></a>\n\nThe oyster mats are laid out in designated areas like a patchwork quilt, connected using concrete doughnuts. Within one year, a single oyster mat will become home to an average of 93 new baby oysters.\n\n<a href="http://darrengriffith.net/wp/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/OysterMat3.png"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-55" alt="OysterMat3" src="http://darrengriffith.net/wp/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/OysterMat3-300x190.png" width="300" height="190" /><a href="http://darrengriffith.net/wp/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/OysterMat4.png"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-56" alt="OysterMat4" src="http://darrengriffith.net/wp/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/OysterMat4-300x250.png" width="300" height="250" /></a></a>\n\nIn its time, the Oyster Restoration Mat Project has used over 36,000 mats to help build 63 restored reefs.Â  This project is almost exclusively volunteer-based, run on the assistance of over 34,000 volunteers.Â  These community members from all across Florida are responsible for everything related to the project.Â  This includes everything from cutting and assembling mats, to drilling shells, to transporting mats to the sites, to deployment of mats to their new location.Â  Thanks to the involvement of the community, we aspire to have deployed 40,000 oyster restoration mats by the end of 2014.\n\n<a href="http://darrengriffith.net/wp/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/OysterMat5.png"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-57" alt="OysterMat5" src="http://darrengriffith.net/wp/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/OysterMat5-300x225.png" width="300" height="225" /></a>\n\n&nbsp;', 'Oyster Mats', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '52-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-04-03 20:32:30', '2014-04-03 20:32:30', '', 52, 'http://brevardoystergardens.org/?p=539', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(540, 3, '2014-04-03 20:32:34', '2014-04-03 20:32:34', 'During the summer months, the oyster restoration team collects the oyster mats volunteers have made at these public events throughout the year. The oyster mats are then deployed in the prepared restoration areas and connected using the concrete doughnuts and zip ties. The restoration sites are then frequently monitored throughout the year and for years to come.\n\n<a href="http://darrengriffith.net/wp/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Deployment1.png"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-72" alt="Deployment1" src="http://darrengriffith.net/wp/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Deployment1-300x236.png" width="300" height="236" /></a><a href="http://darrengriffith.net/wp/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Deployment2.png"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-74" alt="Deployment2" src="http://darrengriffith.net/wp/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Deployment2-300x225.png" width="300" height="225" /></a>\n\n&nbsp;', 'Deployment', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '71-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-04-03 20:32:34', '2014-04-03 20:32:34', '', 71, 'http://brevardoystergardens.org/?p=540', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
