(680, 3, '2014-04-11 00:20:05', '2014-04-11 00:20:05', 'During the summer months, the oyster restoration team collects the oyster mats volunteers have made at these public events throughout the year. The oyster mats are then deployed in the prepared restoration areas and connected using the concrete doughnuts and zip ties. The restoration sites are then frequently monitored throughout the year and for years to come.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://darrengriffith.net/wp/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Deployment2.png"><a href="http://brevardoystergardens.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Deployment11.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-72" alt="Deployment1" src="http://brevardoystergardens.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Deployment11.png" width="608" height="480" /></a></a><a href="http://brevardoystergardens.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Deployment22.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-679" alt="Deployment2" src="http://brevardoystergardens.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Deployment22.png" width="650" height="488" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Deployment', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '71-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-04-11 00:20:05', '2014-04-11 00:20:05', '', 71, 'http://brevardoystergardens.org/?p=680', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
