(809, 5, '2014-06-23 15:33:45', '2014-06-23 15:33:45', '<a href="http://brevardoystergardens.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/why11.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-681" alt="why1" src="http://brevardoystergardens.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/why11.png" width="512" height="270" /></a>\r\n\r\nDid you know oysters can actually swim for the first two weeks of their lives? Adult oysters release their gametes into the water, where they join and create a fertilized egg that will become a free-swimming larvae. For the next two weeks, this oyster larvae is traveling through the Indian River Lagoon looking for a place to live. This is a very important decision because after these two weeks, the oysters are stationary and they will stay in the same location for the rest of their lives.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://brevardoystergardens.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/why21.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-683" alt="why2" src="http://brevardoystergardens.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/why21.jpg" width="676" height="507" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://brevardoystergardens.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/why31.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-684" alt="why3" src="http://brevardoystergardens.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/why31.jpg" width="803" height="504" /></a>\r\n\r\nOysters are gregarious species, meaning they prefer to live among other oysters. As this free-swimming larvae is floating through the lagoon, sometimes for miles, they are looking for other oysters to settle with. They also require a hard substrate to attach to, where they can grow and build their shell composed of calcium. The average life span of the Eastern Oyster, <i>Crassostrea virginica</i>, is approximately 20 years.\r\n\r\nWant more information? Check out these excellent additional educational materials concerning oysters provided by the <a href="http://www.loxahatcheeriver.org/rivercenterflash/slides.html " target="_blank">Loxahatchee River District</a>.', 'Why Oysters?', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '140-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-06-23 15:33:45', '2014-06-23 15:33:45', '', 140, 'http://brevardoystergardens.org/?p=809', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
