thin our community to provide solutions.\r\n\r\n<b>Â </b>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://brevardoystergardens.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/DUCF36__55990.1360004520.1280.1280.jpg"><img class="alignnone  wp-image-918" alt="" src="http://brevardoystergardens.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/DUCF36__55990.1360004520.1280.1280.jpg" width="361" height="361" /></a>\r\n\r\nUse of Oyster Mats for oyster reef restoration was pioneered by <a href="http://biology.cos.ucf.edu/faculty/linda-walters/">Dr. Linda Walters</a>, of the <a href="http://www.ucf.edu/">University of Central Florida</a>, and has proven to be a successful scientific-based restoration technique.Â Together, UCF and Brevard Zoo deploy these mats into Mosquito Lagoon at designated restoration sites and continue to monitor their progress through research and data collection. In addition to oyster mat restoration, University of Central Florida is leading living shoreline stabilization efforts in Canaveral National Seashore and aiming to <a href="http://today.ucf.edu/ucf-app-aims-prevent-boat-mishaps-protect-mosquito-lagoon/">reduce boating collisions</a> with oyster reefs.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a href="http://brevardoystergardens.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Eastern_Florida_State_College_Logo.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-919" alt="" src="http://brevardoystergardens.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Eastern_Florida_State_College_Logo.png" width="357" height="200" /></a>\r\n\r\nThe <a href="http://www.easternflorida.edu/">Eastern Florida State College</a> Environmental Club of the Melbourne Campus seeks to promote environmental stewardship through the service of its members, educate the public on the importance of maintaining a healthy ecosystem through community outreach, and support the Eastern Florida State College Melbourne Campus in its efforts to pursue and maintain a sustainable environment. The club is fulfilling this mission statement through the countless hours of preparation work its members do for oyster gardening workshops, including cutting wire to create oyster habitats. The club will also be conducting water quality monitoring throughout the entirety of the project, which will aid in determining the factors behind survivability of oysters throughout Brevard County.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://brevardoystergardens.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/UF_Logo.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-920" alt="" src="http://brevardoystergardens.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/UF_Logo.jpg" width="1194" height="365" /></a>\r\nThe <a href="http://brevard.ifas.ufl.edu">University Of Florida IFAS</a> Extension Brevard County is partnering with Brevard County and Brevard Zoo to teach waterfront property owners about how to get involved with the Oyster Gardening program. Meanwhile, the <a href="http://www.flseagrant.org/">Florida Sea Grant</a> Extension agent for Brevard County provides educational opportunities and university research-based information on a variety of topics and issues to the citizens of Brevard County.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://brevardoystergardens.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Screen-Shot-2014-07-10-at-10.20.06-AM.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-921" alt="" src="http://brevardoystergardens.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Screen-Shot-2014-07-10-at-10.20.06-AM.png" width="563" height="163" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.modusoperandi.com/">Modus Operandi</a>Â is high-tech software company specializing in delivering technology that helps organizations discover the hidden patterns locked in their data. Modus Operandi employees were involved with the initial development of this website.', 'Our Partners', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '188-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-07-10 14:30:25', '2014-07-10 14:30:25', '', 188, 'http://brevardoystergardens.org/?p=927', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
