(1521, 5, '2016-05-30 16:07:52', '2016-05-30 16:07:52', '[gallery columns="5" link="file" ids="1063,1067,1068,1064,1065"]\r\n\r\nOur oyster restoration team collects oyster mats made by volunteers throughout the year. During the summer months, these mats are deployed across Mosquito Lagoon in prepared restoration areas with guidance from the University of Central Floridaâs Dr. Linda Walters, boat support from the Florida Fish & Wildlife Conservation Commission and IRL National Estuary Program, and the hard workÂ ofÂ many dedicated volunteers. Summer is the perfect time of year for this activity, because itâs during oyster spawning season but before barnacle season, giving young oysters enough time to find restored reefs and settle before barnacles appear to compete with them. And once summer draws to a close, completed restoration sites are frequently monitored throughout the year and for years to come.\r\n\r\n<iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/UHyiAtuK7ag" width="853" height="480" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"></iframe>\r\n\r\nVolunteer opportunities for oyster mat deployment are available each summer, but participants must be at least 16 years of age, and space is limited. To reserve your place on the boat, please register on the <a href="http://brevardoystergardens.org/volunteer/">volunteer</a> page. Once you are registered, you will be provided with information on what to wear, what to bring, and where to meet up with the team. If you have any questions or concerns, please contact <a href="http://mailto:kbrown@brevardzoo.org">Kate Brown</a>. ', 'Help Deploy Oyster Mats', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '71-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-05-30 16:07:52', '2016-05-30 16:07:52', '', 71, 'http://brevardoystergardens.org/71-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
