(18, 'Oyster Gardening Site Visits', '2015-11-03', '2015-12-22', '<p style="text-align: center">Site visit days require driving to about 12 gardening sites around the county and taking counts/measurements on live oysters. We will be outdoors for most of the day, and volunteers need to be able to lift heavy oyster habitats out of the water, which can be strenuous. You will be paired with one of our staff members, who will provide transportation and will show you what to do.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center">We will meet at the front of the <a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/brevard+zoo/@28.2249874,-80.713857,15z/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x0:0x49e05e7c2f44d7a0?sa=X&amp;ved=0CJMBEPwSMA5qFQoTCM6ots24uMcCFcEoHgodScAJ4g" target="_blank">zoo </a>at <strong>8:30 AM</strong> and return sometimeÂ before <strong>5 PM</strong>.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center">Please be sure to<strong>Â bring plenty of water, a lunch sunscreen and plan to wear clothes that you don\\''t mind getting dirty.</strong></p>', 'Recurring', '', 'Karina', 'kvega@brevardzoo.org', 'none', 5, 1, 0, 0, 1, 0, 0, 0),
