(26, 'Reef Monitoring: Brevard', '2016-07-27', '2016-07-29', '<p style="text-align: center">Volunteers Needed to Monitor 2015 Reefs!</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center">Â Please join us and UCF, as we check back up on our very first oyster reefs! Â There are 2 volunteer shifts per day, so if you\\''re up for a half or whole day, of being out on the water, lifting and moving some live oyster bags, we\\''d love to have you!</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center"><strong>July 27-29-- Melbourne Beach</strong></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center">*Event meeting location and map, attire and all other necessary information will be provided in a follow-up e-mail that will be sent out closer to the registration date. If you do not receive this email at least 2 days prior the event, please contact Karina at kvega@brevardzoo.org, or at Office: 321.254.9453 x 441, Work Cell: 321.506.2460.</p>', 'Multi-Day', '', 'Karina Briceno', 'kvega@brevardzoo.org', 'none', 5, 2, 0, 0, 1, 0, 0, 0),
(28, 'Grant Seafood Festival Shell Collection', '2016-03-05', '2016-03-06', '<a href="http://brevardoystergardens.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/2011-01-01-00-121.jpg"><img class=" size-medium wp-image-1478 aligncenter" src="http://brevardoystergardens.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/2011-01-01-00-121-300x225.jpg" alt="2011-01-01 00-121" width="300" height="225" /></a>\r\n\r\nWe need your help to collect oyster shell at the Grant Seafood Festival, coming up on March 5th and 6th, so that we can recycle it for use in our oyster restoration programs! We\\''ll be meeting at the<a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/4580+1st+St,+Grant,+FL+32949/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x88de6b77649b0b8d:0xf28b6e090836c39f?sa=X&amp;ved=0ahUKEwiU-4L8hv3KAhVG9x4KHbvNDvkQ8gEIGzAA" target="_blank"> festival site</a> both days to collect shell from festival-goers in shifts, so be sure to sign up for the shift you\\''d like to work.\r\n<br><br />\r\n<div class="pta-sus-sheet">\r\n\r\nRegistration is <strong>required</strong> to attend this event, and participants must be ages <strong>14 and up</strong>. Participants must alsoÂ <strong><a href="http://brevardoystergardens.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/BZ-Vol-Waiver.doc" target="_blank">print and sign a waiver</a></strong>Â (for those under 18, the waiverÂ will need to beÂ <strong>signed by a guardian</strong>).\r\n\r\nPlease be sure to bring plenty of water, snacks, sunscreen, and bug spray. We also recommend wearing closed-toed shoes and clothes that you don\\''t mind getting dirty.\r\n\r\n</div>', 'Multi-Day', '', 'Kate Brown', 'kbrown@brevardzoo.org', 'none', 7, 1, 0, 0, 1, 0, 0, 0),
(29, 'Reef Building: Melbourne', '2016-07-15', '2016-07-15', '<p style="text-align: center">Reef Building</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center"><a href="http://brevardoystergardens.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/IMG_1671.jpg"><img class="  wp-image-1501 alignnone" src="http://brevardoystergardens.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/IMG_1671-300x193.jpg" alt="IMG_1671" width="307" height="198" /></a></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center">Join us in building the next and largest set of filter-feeding oyster reefs in Brevard County!</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center">**These events will take place outdoors, by or in the lagoon, and will requireÂ <strong>MODERATE to INTENSEÂ </strong>physical labor**</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center"><strong>Event meeting location and map, attire and all other necessary information will be provided in a follow-up e-mail that will be sent out closer to the registration date. If you do not receive this email at least 2 days prior the event, please contact Karina at kvega@brevardzoo.org, or at Office: 321.254.9453 x 441, Work Cell: 321.506.2460.</strong></p>', 'Multi-Day', '', 'Karina Briceno', 'kvega@brevardzoo.org', 'none', 5, 2, 0, 0, 1, 0, 0, 1),
(30, 'Oyster Mat Supply Moving', '2016-05-25', '2016-05-26', '<p><a href="http://brevardoystergardens.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/DSC_0433.jpg"><img class="alignnone wp-image-1509 size-large" src="http://brevardoystergardens.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/DSC_0433-1024x680.jpg" alt="DSC_0433" width="474" height="315" /></a></p>\r\n<p>Since last summer, more than 3,500Â volunteersÂ have helpedÂ us build 1,000 mats that are now ready for deployment up in Mosquito Lagoon! Now, we need to move these mats and additionalÂ supplies out to our newest reefs sites in preparation for restoration.Â </p>\r\n<p>Full event details, including meet-up location and what to bring will be provided in a follow-up e-mail. Â Events will require moderately intense physical labor. Participants must be over the age of 16. Under 18 requires parental supervision. Â </p>', 'Multi-Day', '', 'Kate Brown', 'kbrown@brevardzoo.org', 'none', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, 0, 0),
(31, 'Mat Deployments: Mosquito Lagoon', '2016-06-10', '2016-06-29', '<p><a href="http://brevardoystergardens.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/rakingdeadmargin.jpg"><img class="  wp-image-1513 aligncenter" src="http://brevardoystergardens.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/rakingdeadmargin-300x200.jpg" alt="rakingdeadmargin" width="417" height="278" /></a><a href="http://brevardoystergardens.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/Deployment_May24-16.jpg"><br /><img class="  wp-image-1516 alignnone" src="http://brevardoystergardens.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/P1010189-300x225.jpg" alt="P1010189" width="376" height="282" /><img class="  wp-image-1514 alignnone" src="http://brevardoystergardens.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/Deployment_May24-16-225x300.jpg" alt="Deployment_May24 (16)" width="214" height="285" /></a></p>\r\n<p>Thanks to over 3,500Â volunteers who worked hard throughout the year building 1,000 oyster mats for <strong>Mosquito Lagoon</strong>, it\\''s finally time to kick off <strong>summer mat deployment</strong> season! Â During the month of June, under the direction of UCF scientist Dr. Linda Walters, we\\''ll be restoring oyster reefs by raking out piles of dead oyster shells &amp; anchoring mats to the estuary floor to serve as habitat for new baby oysters recruiting throughout the summer.Â </p>\r\n<div class="pta-sus-sheet">\r\n<p>Full event details, including meet-up location and what to bring will be provided in a follow-up e-mail that will be sent out closer to the restorationÂ date. Â All events will take place in northern Mosquito Lagoon. Events will require moderately intense physical labor in outdoor conditions. Participants must be over the age of 16. Under 18 requires parental supervision. Â </p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'Multi-Day', '', 'Kate Brown', 'KBrown@BrevardZoo.org', 'none', 1, 0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 0, 0);
